
1. The Product Rule: x^n . x^m = x^(n+m)
2. The Quotient Rule: x^n / x^m = x^(n-m)
3. The Power Rule: (x^n)^m = x^(n.m)
4. Power of Zeor: x^0 = 1
5. Negative exponents: x^(-n) = 1/x^n
6. Fractional exponents: x^(1/n) = nâˆš(x)
7. Distribute an exponent over a product: (x.y)^m = (x^m) . (y^m)
8. Distribute an exponent over a quotient: (x/y)^n = (x^n) / (y^n)
